cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SY

This paper proposes a reinforcement learning-based framework for automatically learning an adaptive learning rate schedule for model training. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the experiments are conducted on neural network architectures and image datasets. The paper also mentions non-convex optimization problems, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of reinforcement learning for control suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
